author: slive
msg: A small rewrite/reorganization of the top section of the
httpd.apache.org page.  I cleaned up the writing a little, and
I also put the Netcraft bragging paragraph second.  Sure,
the numbers are impressive, but the goal of the project is
certainly not to maintain high netcraft numbers.  I don't
think it is the first thing that people should read about
the project.

author: trawick
msg: Change mod_rewrite to use apr-util's dbm support for dbm rewrite
maps.
For now, the SDBM dbm flavor is always used.  It won't be compatible
with dbm rewrite maps built for Apache 1.3 until apr-util supports
ndbm and mod_rewrite is changed to prefer ndbm over the built-in
sdbm.

author: jwoolley
msg: Fix a problem whereby RewriteMap prg:'s would get out of sync due to
the inappropriate use of nonblocking reads.  Also get rid of the stderr
altogether since mod_rewrite never uses it.
